<blockquote>
<p><span style="font-size:150%;">Basics</span></p>
<ul>
<li>The GoI must feature in a minimum of five positively-rated mainsite pages with at least three authors contributing.</li>
<li>The GoI must be open to contributions from all site members.</li>
<li>The GoI must have been issued a searchable site tag. More information on requesting tags can be found <strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2219013/tag-suggestion-thread">here</a></strong></li>
<li>The GoI must have a hub page or equivalent, which will be linked to from the GoI hub and the top bar.</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size:150%;">Submitting</span><br />
Make a new post on the <strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2065601/groups-of-interest">GoI Hub discussion page</a></strong> documenting that the group meets the above requirements. An administrator will respond, either approving the GoI or denying it with a provided reason. If denied, the GoI can be re-submitted after the reason(s) are addressed. Administrators will have the final decision on the acceptance of new groups of interest.</p>
<p>Examples of reasons a group may be denied include deletion-range rated articles or if a GoI is derivative of an existing one. If any piece is not within deletion range, the community has decided that the piece fits within the SCP Foundation paradigm.</p>
<p>If a GoI only meets the minimum requirements, it is possible that group may not strike a chord with the community and will need additional work to flesh out its full potential and place in the site-wide worldbuilding. Should a group fall below the minimum requirements, it may be removed after a review by Site Administration.</p>
<p><span style="font-size:150%;"><em>Remember</em></span><br />
It may take several months to create a Group of Interest. While a new GoI can be submitted at any time, writers are encouraged to emphasize quality of content over speed of implementation, to make the in-progress GoI a stronger contender for acceptance.</p>
<p>Groups of Interest should inspire community members to write articles outside of the original seed. Community buy-in is critical to the success of these creations.</p>
<p>Any questions regarding GoI submission can be asked in comments on this page or via wikidot message to a staff member.</p>
</blockquote>
